 -----
 Require Existence of Profiles Specified on the Commandline
 -----
 -----
 2017-09-25
 -----

  When running Maven with one or more unknown profile ids, Maven will give you a warning.
  This rule will actually break the build for that reason.

  Here is how a project should be setup to use this rule

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<project>
  ...
  <build>
    <plugins>
      ...
      <plugin>
        <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
        <artifactId>maven-enforcer-plugin</artifactId>
        <version>${project.version}</version>
        <executions>
          <execution>
            <id>enforce</id>
            <configuration>
              <rules>
                <requireProfileIdsExist/>
              </rules>
            </configuration>
            <goals>
              <goal>enforce</goal>
            </goals>
          </execution>
        </executions>
      </plugin>
      ...
    </plugins>
  </build>
  ...
</project>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  